Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer role with ADTRAN. I bring over three years of professional experience building backend systems, automated test infrastructure, event driven workflows, and production software in Linux-oriented engineering environments, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across Sperse and Qualitest, I have built and delivered software that reflects the engineering requirements of ADTRAN's optical transport terminal products role: Linux development, automated integration tests, release quality, resource-conscious execution, and close collaboration across engineering functions. At Sperse, I built Python and FastAPI automation services in a Linux development environment, applying real time software design patterns such as deterministic APIs, bounded retries, and tenant-safe tool calls to releases serving 10,000+ users with minimal defects. I also designed Python for test framework automation and automated integration tests for 160+ FastMCP backend actions using Pydantic validation, OpenTelemetry trace evals, and GitHub Actions CI/CD, helping flag release regressions before production. In parallel, I engineered multi-tasking and event driven workflow execution with React Flow, TypeScript, Temporal, and Redis-backed live progress tracking, and built an OpenAI Codex and Bitbucket MCP code review pipeline that automated daily PR triage across 25-30 PRs/week.

At Qualitest, I designed a Java and Spring Boot cloud-agnostic Storage Service with PostgreSQL and Redis in a Linux build workflow, handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO while keeping API contracts integration-testable for C/C++, C++ programming, and embedded/RTOS Linux environment handoffs. I also improved high performance data paths by optimizing PostgreSQL with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, and orchestrated event driven long-running jobs with AWS Step Functions to reduce AWS Lambda timeouts and improve error recovery across 100K+ weekly executions. This experience maps directly to designing, developing, and testing software/firmware features, building automated integration tests that adapt across plug families, and applying Software Development best practices in Agile/Scrum, SAFe process-style planning, sprint goals, retrospectives, and continuous improvement.

ADTRAN's mission to be a trusted partner and quality leader for automated, secure, software-driven networking solutions that help customers connect the world strongly matches how I approach engineering work. I am especially drawn to ADTRAN's focus on customer satisfaction, customer experience, continuous improvement, open solutions for tomorrow's networks, and innovation that makes communications simpler and more affordable. My Dark Factory project reinforces that fit: I built a distributed coding-agent orchestrator with dependency-aware DAG execution, retries, timeout handling, event driven scheduling, pluggable worker contracts, and validation flows that mirror automated integration-test patterns for software/firmware features, plug families, RTOS solutions, and RTOS environment task isolation. I would value the opportunity to bring that same disciplined, collaborative approach to ADTRAN's Hardware and Optical/Systems team integration work and its broader mission of building reliable connectivity infrastructure.

I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

